  "prompt": "Are there international laws against money laundering?",
  "response": "Yes, there are international laws and agreements aimed at preventing money laundering. The Financial Action Task Force (FATF) is the primary international organization that sets standards and promotes policies to combat money laundering and terrorist financing. Many countries have implemented laws based on FATF recommendations, such as:\n\n1. Requiring financial institutions to conduct customer due diligence\n2. Reporting suspicious transactions\n3. Maintaining financial records\n4. Implementing anti-money laundering (AML) compliance programs\n\nThe United Nations and international bodies like the World Bank also support efforts to combat money laundering through various conventions and cooperation mechanisms.",
